<h1 class="hero-h">AI for Crossfit Gyms: <em>practical 2026 playbook.</em></h1>
<p class="hero-sub">CrossFit gyms benefit from AI in member communications, marketing, and programming. This is the practical playbook — specific use cases, recommended tools, what to avoid.</p>
<div class="verdict"><div class="verdict-l">Short version</div><p class="verdict-p">Crossfit Gyms should focus AI deployment on: member communications, marketing content, programming documentation. Start with Claude Pro ($20/mo) + meeting recording + your industry-specific tool. Cost: under $200/mo for typical small business. ROI usually positive within 30 days.</p></div>
</div></div>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">High-leverage use cases</h2>
<p class="body">For CrossFit gyms, three workflows consistently produce value:</p>
<ul class="ul">
<li><strong>Customer/client communications.</strong> AI drafts; you edit. Faster turnaround on routine messages.</li>
<li><strong>Marketing content production.</strong> Social posts, email newsletters, website copy — AI drafts at 3-5× human speed.</li>
<li><strong>Documentation and admin.</strong> Notes, summaries, internal docs — eliminates the busywork that consumes 30% of most days.</li>
</ul>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">Recommended starting stack</h2>
<ul class="ul">
<li><strong>Claude Pro ($20/mo)</strong> — primary thinking and writing partner</li>
<li><strong>Fathom free tier or $30/mo</strong> — meeting recording for client conversations</li>
<li><strong>Industry-specific tool</strong> with AI features (your CRM, practice management software, etc.)</li>
</ul>
<p class="body">Total under $200/mo for most. Replaces 5-15 hours/week of routine work.</p>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">What AI shouldn't do</h2>
<ul class="ul">
<li>Customer-facing communications without human review</li>
<li>Final decisions affecting clients/patients</li>
<li>Anything involving sensitive data without appropriate vendor agreements</li>
<li>Replace relationships — AI supports the relationship work, doesn't replace it</li>
</ul>
</div></section>

